    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Simon Evans worked as a chief officer in the magistrates’ courts service, and served as a justices’ chief executive and a justices’ clerk in Cumbria. He subsequently took office as the first Area Director of Her Majesty’s Courts Service (HMCS) in the region.</p>

<h2 id="career">Career</h2>

<p>Simon left HMCS in 2007 to pursue a portfolio career, working as a Deputy Traffic Commissioner, a Fee Paid Judge on the Social Entitlement Chamber, a Lay Member (Chair) of the Nursing and Midwifery Council’s Fitness to Practice Panel and an Independent Member (Chair) of the Parole Board for England and Wales. Simon previously worked as a management consultant supporting and advising the Croatian Government and its courts on its application for EU membership and as a former member of the Judicial Studies Board.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4083">
            <h1 id="traffic-commissioner-for-the-north-west-of-england">Traffic Commissioner for the north west of England </h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>Responsibilities are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the licensing of the operators of Heavy Goods Vehicles (<abbr title="Heavy Goods Vehicles">HGVs</abbr>) and of buses and coaches known as Public Service Vehicles (<abbr title="Public Service Vehicles">PSVs</abbr>)</li>
  <li>the registration of local bus services</li>
  <li>granting vocational licences and taking action against drivers of <abbr title="Heavy Goods Vehicles">HGVs</abbr> and <abbr title="Public Service Vehicles">PSVs</abbr>
</li>
</ul>

</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/traffic-commissioners">Traffic Commissioners for Great Britain</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>      </div>




